div.h1: VDBE EXECUTION TRACE: Query Flattening & Runtime Lifecycle

p.code: SELECT name FROM users WHERE id > 100

ul.li: Filter Inversion: SQL id > 100 is compiled as Le 100 (Less or Equal).
If comparison is true, we jump over the ResultRow instruction to the Next loop, effectively skipping the record.

g.text: Init | P1:0 | P2:8 | P3:0 | Jump to end for init logic
OpenRead | P1:0 | P2:2 | P3:0 | Open cursor 0 on root page 2
Rewind | P1:0 | P2:8 | P3:0 | Move to start, jump to 8 if empty
Column | P1:0 | P2:0 | P3:1 | Extract 'id' (col 0) -> R1
Le | P1:1 | P2:7 | P3:100 | If R1 <= 100, jump to addr 7 (SKIP)
Column | P1:0 | P2:1 | P3:2 | Extract 'name' (col 1) -> R2
ResultRow | P1:2 | P2:1 | P3:0 | Emit result from R2
Next | P1:0 | P2:3 | P3:0 | Advance cursor, jump to 3 if rows
Halt | P1:0 | P2:0 | P3:0 | Execution Finished
